subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks.
Cacostola opitzi
sp. nov. is similar to
C. variegata
(see photographs of the holotype at Bezark 2019a ) by the lower eye lobes being shorter, slightly longer than the genae (nearly two and one-half times genal length in
C. variegata
), antenna shorter (distinctly longer in male of
C. variegata
), and metatibiae distinctly tumid (not so in male of
C. variegata
). It differs from
C. clorinda
by the antennomere IV being distinctly longer than III (slightly longer in male of
C. clorinda
), antennomeres distinctly annulated (not so in
C. clorinda
), and elytra without a dark central band on the basal half (present in
C. clorinda
).
